  "questions": [
    {
      "text": "What is the most probable reason for the swelling in the tonsils of a 40-year-old woman who has difficulty swallowing food, no past medical history of fever, sore throat, or smoking, but a family history of Marfan's syndrome in her father, and shows unilateral swelling of the tonsils along with pulsation upon oral examination?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 0,
          "text": "Extracranial internal carotid artery aneurysm"
        },
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Intracranial external carotid artery aneurysm"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Extracranial external carotid artery aneurysm"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Intracranial internal carotid artery aneurysm"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 0,
      "solution": "<p><strong>Correct Answer: A) <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"ae83c0cf40169277718732a723c610\">Extracranial</span> Internal <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"8593e48e0416927771834eaedb0bfd\">Carotid</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"a66cd3adaa1692777182e77cb23021\">Artery</span> Aneurysm</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Explanation:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>The <strong>unilateral <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"e670f25fb7169277720087be88cc56\">tonsillar</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"e3d212ebd316927771996e0c472d4a\">swelling</span> with pulsation</strong> suggests a <strong>vascular etiology</strong>, and the presence of <strong>Marfan’s syndrome</strong> in the family history increases the likelihood of an <strong>aneurysm</strong> due to <strong>connective tissue disorder</strong>.</li>\n\t<li>The <strong>extracranial internal <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"8593e48e0416927771834eaedb0bfd\">carotid</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"a66cd3adaa1692777182e77cb23021\">artery</span> (ICA) aneurysm</strong> is a rare but recognized cause of <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"e670f25fb7169277720087be88cc56\">tonsillar</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"e3d212ebd316927771996e0c472d4a\">swelling</span> and can <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"efaf9e0192169277719278711f7f74\">mimic</span> a mass lesion.</li>\n\t<li>It is located <strong>medially to the tonsil</strong> and can be identified by <strong>pulsation</strong> on examination.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Extracranial Internal <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"8593e48e0416927771834eaedb0bfd\">Carotid</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"a66cd3adaa1692777182e77cb23021\">Artery</span> Aneurysm</strong></p>\n\n<table cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse\">\n\t<tbody>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Feature</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Description</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Cause</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Weakening of ICA wall (due to <strong>atherosclerosis, Marfan’s syndrome, Ehlers-Danlos syndrome, infections, or trauma</strong>)</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Symptoms</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>1. <strong>Unilateral <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"e670f25fb7169277720087be88cc56\">tonsillar</span> swelling</strong></p>\n\n\t\t\t<p>2. <strong>Dysphagia</strong> (difficulty swallowing)</p>\n\n\t\t\t<p>3. <strong>Pulsation on oral exam</strong></p>\n\n\t\t\t<p>4. <strong>Absence of infection or <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"9d21dd5d3116927771907405b181bc\">inflammatory</span> signs</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Risk Factors</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Connective tissue disorders (Marfan's, Ehlers-Danlos), atherosclerosis, hypertension</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Complications</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Rupture, thrombosis, stroke, or <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"6b7b5460171692777185e6e2475f8c\">cranial</span> nerve compression</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Diagnosis</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>CT/MR angiography, Doppler ultrasound</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Treatment</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Surgical repair or <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"0dc32a9edf1692777187a82b199252\">endovascular</span> stenting</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p><strong>Incorrect Options:</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Intracranial External <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"8593e48e0416927771834eaedb0bfd\">Carotid</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"a66cd3adaa1692777182e77cb23021\">Artery</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"f2c92eaffe16927771819978aa5666\">Aneurysm</span> (Option B):</strong> is incorrect because the <strong>external <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"8593e48e0416927771834eaedb0bfd\">carotid</span> artery</strong> does not run close to the tonsils, and <strong>intracranial aneurysms do not present as <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"e670f25fb7169277720087be88cc56\">tonsillar</span> swelling</strong>.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Extracranial External <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"8593e48e0416927771834eaedb0bfd\">Carotid</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"a66cd3adaa1692777182e77cb23021\">Artery</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"f2c92eaffe16927771819978aa5666\">Aneurysm</span> (Option C):</strong> is incorrect because the <strong>external <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"8593e48e0416927771834eaedb0bfd\">carotid</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"a66cd3adaa1692777182e77cb23021\">artery</span> runs laterally in the neck</strong>, not medially near the tonsils.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Intracranial Internal <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"8593e48e0416927771834eaedb0bfd\">Carotid</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"a66cd3adaa1692777182e77cb23021\">Artery</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"f2c92eaffe16927771819978aa5666\">Aneurysm</span> (Option D):</strong> is incorrect because an <strong>intracranial ICA <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"f2c92eaffe16927771819978aa5666\">aneurysm</span> presents with stroke-like symptoms (headache, visual disturbances, or <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"6b7b5460171692777185e6e2475f8c\">cranial</span> nerve palsies)</strong> rather than <strong>tonsillar swelling</strong>.</p>",
