    {
      "text": "Which is the false statement among the following for the condition given in the picture?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 0,
          "text": "Retention cyst of major salivary glands"
        },
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Most common site is lower lip"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "It is a benign condition"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Treatment is surgical excision"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 0,
      "solution": "<p><strong>Answer: A) <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"b668aed705169277719744b6db8f8e\">Retention</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"1405ad7b46169277718580acad7562\">cyst</span> of major salivary glands</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Explanation:</strong></p>\n\n<p>Based on the image<strong>, </strong>the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"d5e7bb15851692777191b39417c26a\">lesion</span> is most likely a <strong>mucocele</strong>, which commonly presents as a bluish, <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"1adaaa6ded16927772023e7fe0c856\">fluctuant</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"e3d212ebd316927771996e0c472d4a\">swelling</span> on the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"534123d47916927771914a66769a37\">lower lip</span> due to <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"ab75ea330616927771938a64f8ebd6\">mucus</span> accumulation from minor salivary glands.</p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>\n\t<p>Mucoceles are typically <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"b668aed705169277719744b6db8f8e\">retention</span> or <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"f0c6fefae41692777187c76a6f65f6\">extravasation</span> cysts of the <strong>minor salivary glands</strong>, not major ones.</p>\n\t</li>\n\t<li>\n\t<p>Hence the statement \"Retention <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"1405ad7b46169277718580acad7562\">cyst</span> of major salivary glands<strong>\" </strong>is<strong> false</strong></p>\n\t</li>\n\t<li>A <strong>retention cyst</strong> of the <strong>major salivary glands</strong> typically forms in the ductal system due to the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"43c30dc8c8169277718317ffb7dea0\">blockage</span> of the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"6198b5f22b16927771867e4ef8108f\">duct</span> or ductal dilation.</li>\n\t<li>The most common sites for <strong>retention cysts of the major salivary glands</strong> are the <strong>parotid gland</strong> and the <strong>submandibular gland</strong>, not the <strong>lower lip</strong>, which is a common site for <strong>minor salivary <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"4744bb90c21692777188c8957f9faa\">gland</span> cysts</strong>.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3><strong>Retention <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"1405ad7b46169277718580acad7562\">Cyst</span> of Salivary Glands</strong></h3>\n\n<table cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse\">\n\t<tbody>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Feature</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Description</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Cause</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Blockage or damage to the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"6198b5f22b16927771867e4ef8108f\">duct</span> system of the salivary <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"4744bb90c21692777188c8957f9faa\">gland</span> leads to <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"1405ad7b46169277718580acad7562\">cyst</span> formation.</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Location</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Major salivary glands</strong> (parotid, submandibular, and <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"75089cc39e1692777199b8933bd249\">sublingual</span> glands) for <strong>major</strong> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"b668aed705169277719744b6db8f8e\">retention</span> cysts.</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Minor Salivary Glands</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Most often found on the <strong>lower lip</strong>, <strong>buccal mucosa</strong>, or <strong>palate</strong> for <strong>minor salivary glands</strong>.</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Treatment</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Surgical <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"20b3ce06c5169277718756ee95c1e9\">excision</span> is the standard treatment to remove the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"1405ad7b46169277718580acad7562\">cyst</span> and prevent recurrence.</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Diagnosis</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Clinical examination and <strong>ultrasound or sialography</strong> for confirmation.</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p><strong>Most common site is <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"534123d47916927771914a66769a37\">lower lip</span> (Option B): </strong>This is true. The <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"534123d47916927771914a66769a37\">lower lip</span> is the most frequent site for mucoceles</p>\n\n<p><strong>Is a <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"1bbae82f1f16927771824f797639fa\">benign</span> condition: (Option C):</strong> This is true. Mucoceles are <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"1bbae82f1f16927771824f797639fa\">benign</span> lesions.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Treatment is <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"81d12f9cb01692777199e44ff3f3c1\">surgical</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"20b3ce06c5169277718756ee95c1e9\">excision</span> (Option D):</strong> This is true. The standard treatment for mucoceles is <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"81d12f9cb01692777199e44ff3f3c1\">surgical</span> excision.</p>",
